==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitesmith
<hw>White"smith`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who works in tinned or galvanized iron, or white iron; a
tinsmith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A worker in iron who finishes or polishes the work,
in distinction from one who forges it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitester</ent>⟦br⟧
